Title : Ieud Hill Church
Text : [[File:Ieud deal.jpg|thumb|Ieud Hill Church]]
The '''Ieud Hill Church''' ({{lang-ro|Biserica din Ieud Deal}}), dedicated to the Nativity of the Virgin, is a [[Romanian Orthodox]] church in [[Ieud]] Commune, [[Maramureș County]], [[Romania]]. Built in the early 17th century, it is one of eight buildings that make up the [[wooden churches of Maramureș]] [[UNESCO World Heritage Site]],<ref>[http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/904 Wooden Churches of Maramureș] at the UNESCO site</ref> and is also listed as a [[Monument istoric|historic monument]] by the country's [[Ministry of Culture and Religious Affairs (Romania)|Ministry of Culture and Religious Affairs]].<ref>{{ro icon}} [http://www.patrimoniu.ro/images/LMI/LMI-2010_MM.pdf Lista Monumentelor Istorice 2010: Judeţul Maramureş], p.1712</ref> Its name comes from the fact that it is located on a hill, and is used to distinguish it from the [[Ieud Valley Church]]. 

